```

The proof goal is to show that `lineDerivCLM v T` is a continuous linear map. The specific goal is:
`∀ (m : ℝ) (x : E), (@DFunLike.coe ... (lineDerivCLM v T) ... ContinuousLinearMap.funLike ... (m • x)) f = (RingHom.id ℝ) m • (@DFunLike.coe ... (lineDerivCLM v T) ... ContinuousLinearMap.funLike ... x) f`

This is essentially showing that `lineDerivCLM v T` is a linear map when `E` is finite-dimensional. The proof strategy will be to show that `lineDerivCLM v T` is linear and continuous.

